diment is it capable of binding together human beings in such a way that partisan attachments are dissolved and a new era of history, free for once of the lethal repetition of collective violence, can be entered into.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGood and evilxPhilosophy. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 0aViolencexPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aDeBevoise, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363150240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631502423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631502/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPHb2022